issue.body:
The setup shown in https://kubevirt.io/user-guide/user_workloads/startup_scripts/ where you can run

```
# install Qemu Tools (Drivers)
Start-Process msiexec -Wait -ArgumentList '/i e:\virtio-win-gt-x64.msi /qn /passive /norestart'
```

isn't working anymore as `virtio-win-gt-x64.msi` seems to be missing from the latest `virtio-container-disk`.
Can you confirm this is the case, and if so, suggest any workaround?

chore(*): porting notes from (Algebraic)?(Geometry|Topology) and CategoryTheory (#28518)

Address a lot of porting notes in AlgebraicGeometry, AlgebraicTopology and Geometry folders. Also a few in CategoryTheory that I noticed as I went through the other ones. A lot of the notes are about `simp` or instances not seeing through `def`s, which is intended behaviour.

feat(MeasureTheory): add `Star`, `InvolutiveStar` and `TrivialStar` instances for `AEEqFun` (#28123)

We add `Filter.EventuallyEq.star`, `StronglyMeasurable.star` and `AEStronglyMeasurable.star` in order to define `Star (Œ± ‚Üí‚Çò[Œº] R)`, `InvolutiveStar (Œ± ‚Üí‚Çò[Œº] R)`, and `TrivialStar (Œ± ‚Üí‚Çò[Œº] R)`.

These results are on the way to a `CStarAlgebra` instance for L^\infty.



Co-authored-by: Jon Bannon <59937998+JonBannon@users.noreply.github.com>

refactor: deprecate all the material in the CGT repo (#28063)

A few months ago, we created the [`combinatorial-games`](https://github.com/vihdzp/combinatorial-games) repo, downstreaming the material on combinatorial games, nimbers, and surreals. We've since expanded on this material quite substantially, leaving the Mathlib development quite outdated. Since this is not used elsewhere in Mathlib (and is very unlikely to ever be), we deprecate everything, and link to the relevant files in the new repo.

See [Zulip](https://leanprover.zulipchat.com/#narrow/channel/287929-mathlib4/topic/Repository.20for.20combinatorial.20games/near/533203358).

issue.body:
The setup shown in https://kubevirt.io/user-guide/user_workloads/startup_scripts/ where you can run

```
# install Qemu Tools (Drivers)
Start-Process msiexec -Wait -ArgumentList '/i e:\virtio-win-gt-x64.msi /qn /passive /norestart'
```

isn't working anymore as `virtio-win-gt-x64.msi` seems to be missing from the latest `virtio-container-disk`.
Can you confirm this is the case, and if so, suggest any workaround?

feat: add advanced CLI options and benchmarking improvements

New features:
- --runs N: Average results over multiple runs for stability
- --csv-only: Skip text log file, only output to CSV
- --quiet: CI/CD friendly output without colors/emojis
- Use np.empty() instead of np.random.rand() for faster allocation
- Replace optimized arr.sum() with memory sampling for realistic bandwidth test
- Improved error handling and user experience

Examples:
- python memory_benchmark.py --quiet --csv-only --runs 3
- python memory_benchmark.py --sizes 1024 2048 --runs 5
